00:00:28.205 --> 00:00:29.580 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
Women complain

00:00:29.580 --> 00:00:32.340 align:middle line:10%
that men don't hear them,
and men complain that women

00:00:32.340 --> 00:00:33.740 align:middle line:10%
don't give them space.

00:00:33.740 --> 00:00:37.150 align:middle line:84%
According to Arjuna Aradagh
and John Gray in their newest

00:00:37.150 --> 00:00:39.940 align:middle line:84%
book "Conscious Men," these
are legitimate complaints

00:00:39.940 --> 00:00:41.800 align:middle line:84%
because we're wired
totally differently.

00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:45.120 align:middle line:84%
It's all down to oxytocin
and testosterone.

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.020 align:middle line:84%
And of course, a little
bit of re-education

00:00:47.020 --> 00:00:50.520 align:middle line:84%
helps, right?
[CHUCKLING] Welcome.

00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:52.680 align:middle line:84%
Arjuna, how did
you and John decide

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:54.690 align:middle line:84%
to go into collaboration
to begin with?

00:00:54.690 --> 00:00:56.190 align:middle line:10%
>>ARJUNA ARDAGH:
Well, actually I've

00:00:56.190 --> 00:01:00.900 align:middle line:10%
known John Gray for more than 30
years, maybe close to 40 years.

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:03.350 align:middle line:10%
We met when we
were both involved

00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:06.760 align:middle line:10%
with Transcendental Meditation
and Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:10.150 align:middle line:84%
John Gray was the secretary
to Maharishi Mahesh Yogi years

00:01:10.150 --> 00:01:12.850 align:middle line:90%
ago when I was still a teenager.

00:01:12.850 --> 00:01:15.000 align:middle line:90%
But we connected more recently.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.800 align:middle line:84%
We've been part of the
same men's group in Marin,

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:22.050 align:middle line:84%
for Marin County, California,
for eight years now.

00:01:22.050 --> 00:01:24.890 align:middle line:84%
And it was really out of being
part of the same men's group.

00:01:24.890 --> 00:01:26.580 align:middle line:84%
I would stay at his
house sometimes.

00:01:26.580 --> 00:01:29.210 align:middle line:84%
We would get into talking
about our men's group,

00:01:29.210 --> 00:01:31.900 align:middle line:84%
then more broadly
about men in general.

00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:35.370 align:middle line:84%
And out of those
conversations-- I

00:01:35.370 --> 00:01:38.190 align:middle line:84%
would go to stay with him
because I lived too far

00:01:38.190 --> 00:01:40.860 align:middle line:90%
away to drive home afterwards.

00:01:40.860 --> 00:01:44.560 align:middle line:84%
I'd go stay with him, and we'd
have a cup of tea at 10:00 PM,

00:01:44.560 --> 00:01:47.180 align:middle line:84%
and we'd still be talking
at 2:30 in the night.

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:49.777 align:middle line:84%
And the third time
this happened, we said,

00:01:49.777 --> 00:01:50.860 align:middle line:90%
why didn't we record this?

00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:53.060 align:middle line:84%
We're saying things that
have not been said before.

00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:56.120 align:middle line:84%
So that was how the whole
collaboration started.

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:58.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What do you what
is your men's group in Marin?

00:01:58.940 --> 00:02:00.200 align:middle line:90%
He's in Mill Valley, right?

00:02:00.200 --> 00:02:00.500 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:02:00.500 --> 00:02:01.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:02.155 align:middle line:90%
I used to live there.

00:02:02.155 --> 00:02:03.590 align:middle line:90%
I just love Mill Valley.

00:02:03.590 --> 00:02:07.950 align:middle line:84%
What is the men's
group dedicated to?

00:02:07.950 --> 00:02:10.780 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well, I
think any men's group--

00:02:10.780 --> 00:02:14.340 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHING] It's a funny thing
to talk about to a woman,

00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:16.740 align:middle line:84%
actually, because it's--
any men's group, I think,

00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:19.580 align:middle line:84%
is really dedicated to an
opportunity for men to support

00:02:19.580 --> 00:02:23.160 align:middle line:84%
each other in an
environment that's just men.

00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:27.000 align:middle line:84%
And actually in our book
"Conscious Men," probably

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.040 align:middle line:84%
the one recommendation
that we make in the book

00:02:30.040 --> 00:02:34.190 align:middle line:84%
that we feel would apply, would
be good for absolutely any man

00:02:34.190 --> 00:02:36.050 align:middle line:84%
at all, is to be part
of a men's group.

00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:37.370 align:middle line:90%
It's phenomenal.

00:02:37.370 --> 00:02:39.680 align:middle line:84%
Every week or two
weeks or every month

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.800 align:middle line:84%
to spend a couple of
hours or three hours

00:02:41.800 --> 00:02:44.400 align:middle line:84%
where you're just in
a circle of men-- it's

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:45.700 align:middle line:90%
amazing what happens.

00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:46.810 align:middle line:90%
It's the same for women.

00:02:46.810 --> 00:02:49.840 align:middle line:84%
When you actually get into
a single-gender environment

00:02:49.840 --> 00:02:53.970 align:middle line:84%
for a little while,
something really relaxes back

00:02:53.970 --> 00:02:56.040 align:middle line:84%
into a recognition
of-- [EXHALES]--

00:02:56.040 --> 00:02:58.567 align:middle line:84%
this is what the masculine
is like when it's not

00:02:58.567 --> 00:02:59.900 align:middle line:90%
in relationship to the feminine.

00:02:59.900 --> 00:03:02.090 align:middle line:84%
It's very, very
important for men

00:03:02.090 --> 00:03:05.740 align:middle line:84%
to have that, particular today
when we've got so much blending

00:03:05.740 --> 00:03:09.592 align:middle line:84%
of gender roles, which is a
good thing, that all of us

00:03:09.592 --> 00:03:12.050 align:middle line:84%
get to explore our masculine
and feminine side more than we

00:03:12.050 --> 00:03:13.357 align:middle line:90%
did in previous generations.

00:03:13.357 --> 00:03:15.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's actually a really
good thing now and then

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:17.399 align:middle line:84%
to have a break and
just be men together.

00:03:17.399 --> 00:03:18.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You know, it's funny.

00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:20.750 align:middle line:84%
I had dinner with
someone last night

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:28.790 align:middle line:84%
who is struggling in terms
of making a living at exactly

00:03:28.790 --> 00:03:32.490 align:middle line:84%
this, at trying to
help men go deeper

00:03:32.490 --> 00:03:35.310 align:middle line:84%
into themselves and for
men to gather together

00:03:35.310 --> 00:03:37.540 align:middle line:84%
and getting men to
even gather together.

00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:39.620 align:middle line:84%
And he's been at this
for years and years.

00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:42.420 align:middle line:84%
And I told him I'd be
interviewing you today,

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.190 align:middle line:84%
and he said, what's
interesting is

00:03:45.190 --> 00:03:47.380 align:middle line:84%
to me that that's
not in their nature,

00:03:47.380 --> 00:03:49.240 align:middle line:90%
joining together in a group.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:51.950 align:middle line:84%
I don't know any men where
that's in their nature.

00:03:51.950 --> 00:03:54.450 align:middle line:84%
It's something that would be a
conscious choice that they're

00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:56.500 align:middle line:90%
doing for purpose.

00:03:56.500 --> 00:04:01.708 align:middle line:84%
And so it's almost like kind of
swimming upstream, so to speak.

00:04:01.708 --> 00:04:03.791 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: That's a very
interesting point, Regina.

00:04:03.791 --> 00:04:08.320 align:middle line:84%
And I think I would want to
slightly edit what you said.

00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:09.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Sure.

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:11.030 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I'd say
it's definitely very

00:04:11.030 --> 00:04:12.300 align:middle line:90%
much not in our conditioning.

00:04:12.300 --> 00:04:14.930 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's in our nature
or not is a different thing.

00:04:14.930 --> 00:04:16.980 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting
the conditioning,

00:04:16.980 --> 00:04:23.500 align:middle line:84%
because when men put energy
into being with other men,

00:04:23.500 --> 00:04:27.420 align:middle line:84%
it means they're putting value
on bonding with other men.

00:04:27.420 --> 00:04:31.860 align:middle line:84%
Now, what's the message
we got from our fathers

00:04:31.860 --> 00:04:34.420 align:middle line:84%
and forefathers about
making relationship

00:04:34.420 --> 00:04:35.940 align:middle line:90%
with other men primary?

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:41.590 align:middle line:84%
We were conditioned with
homophobia, basically, right?

00:04:41.590 --> 00:04:43.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's hard
to believe, but I

00:04:43.370 --> 00:04:47.670 align:middle line:84%
think until 1965, which
was within my lifetime,

00:04:47.670 --> 00:04:51.760 align:middle line:84%
homosexuality was illegal
in England, right?

00:04:51.760 --> 00:04:53.270 align:middle line:90%
It was only legalized--

00:04:53.270 --> 00:04:55.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yet practiced widely.

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:57.460 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Now, of course,
many marry other men.

00:04:57.460 --> 00:05:00.620 align:middle line:84%
But for the first
seven years of my life

00:05:00.620 --> 00:05:03.610 align:middle line:84%
or eight years of my life,
I was told that for a man

00:05:03.610 --> 00:05:05.530 align:middle line:90%
to love another man is illegal.

00:05:05.530 --> 00:05:07.510 align:middle line:90%
You can go to prison for it.

00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And then if we get into
kind of immoral and not

00:05:09.960 --> 00:05:12.720 align:middle line:84%
fit in the eyes of God, I mean,
we're way, way over the edge

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:13.720 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:05:13.720 --> 00:05:16.290 align:middle line:84%
So we grew up to believe
that getting too close

00:05:16.290 --> 00:05:18.090 align:middle line:90%
to another man was dangerous.

00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:21.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's a conditioning that
many of us, we have to reverse.

00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:25.220 align:middle line:84%
And we have to recognize
that of course as men there's

00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:28.840 align:middle line:84%
a tremendous nourishment and
value to bonding with a woman

00:05:28.840 --> 00:05:31.140 align:middle line:84%
and, maybe if you're
heterosexual to being married.

00:05:31.140 --> 00:05:33.630 align:middle line:84%
There's a tremendous value
to being a father, bonding

00:05:33.630 --> 00:05:34.560 align:middle line:90%
with your children.

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:37.420 align:middle line:84%
There's a tremendous value
to creating good teamwork

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:38.950 align:middle line:90%
with other coworkers.

00:05:38.950 --> 00:05:43.030 align:middle line:84%
But actually putting value,
putting value on relationship

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:44.840 align:middle line:84%
with another man or
other men, that's

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:46.900 align:middle line:84%
something we have to
decondition ourselves

00:05:46.900 --> 00:05:48.260 align:middle line:90%
to be able to see as important.

00:05:48.260 --> 00:05:49.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, exactly.

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:52.790 align:middle line:84%
And I agree with that,
as someone observing

00:05:52.790 --> 00:05:56.290 align:middle line:84%
from the outside, obviously,
and also the hypocrisy

00:05:56.290 --> 00:05:59.490 align:middle line:84%
and what that created by
way of cognitive disconnect

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:01.390 align:middle line:84%
with in England, for
example, with boys

00:06:01.390 --> 00:06:04.370 align:middle line:84%
in public-- "public" meaning
private in our parlance--

00:06:04.370 --> 00:06:07.437 align:middle line:84%
school, where
homosexuality was common.

00:06:07.437 --> 00:06:10.020 align:middle line:84%
Even if you weren't-- you didn't
have to be homosexual to have

00:06:10.020 --> 00:06:14.560 align:middle line:84%
a sexual experience with another
boy or a teacher or your music

00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:17.140 align:middle line:90%
teacher, whomever.

00:06:17.140 --> 00:06:20.040 align:middle line:84%
And I know with a lot
of boys that created

00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:22.270 align:middle line:90%
a lot of damage and confusion.

00:06:22.270 --> 00:06:25.070 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah, well, it
was commonly practiced

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:27.315 align:middle line:90%
but not in any sense condoned.

00:06:27.315 --> 00:06:28.115 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:06:28.115 --> 00:06:28.470 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:06:28.470 --> 00:06:29.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So it
was something that

00:06:29.370 --> 00:06:31.660 align:middle line:84%
happened with a tremendous
amount of guilt and shame

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:31.950 align:middle line:90%
and tension.

00:06:31.950 --> 00:06:32.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:06:32.750 --> 00:06:34.610 align:middle line:84%
And that created
a lot of problems.

00:06:34.610 --> 00:06:37.000 align:middle line:84%
And then yet at
the same time, when

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:39.050 align:middle line:84%
you talk to men, older
men, for example--

00:06:39.050 --> 00:06:43.280 align:middle line:84%
I notice my dad's generation--
what were the great years?

00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:47.170 align:middle line:84%
And they'd be like, well,
World War II or the Korean War,

00:06:47.170 --> 00:06:47.971 align:middle line:90%
where men had to--

00:06:47.971 --> 00:06:49.303 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: --bond with other men.

00:06:49.303 --> 00:06:52.170 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --practice courage
and reliance upon one another.

00:06:52.170 --> 00:06:53.970 align:middle line:84%
Those were the great
moments in life.

00:06:53.970 --> 00:06:57.430 align:middle line:84%
But to get together in a
group and talk about things

00:06:57.430 --> 00:06:58.660 align:middle line:90%
is a whole different thing.

00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:01.000 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well, this is
a really important point

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:02.670 align:middle line:90%
that you're focusing on here.

00:07:02.670 --> 00:07:05.070 align:middle line:84%
It's probably one of
the strongest reasons

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:10.430 align:middle line:84%
to write this book, is that most
of us as men, we kind of need

00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:11.360 align:middle line:90%
a rethink on this.

00:07:11.360 --> 00:07:13.950 align:middle line:84%
We need to become conscious,
anyway, of our needs

00:07:13.950 --> 00:07:17.100 align:middle line:84%
and realize that bonding deeply
with other men for the sake

00:07:17.100 --> 00:07:20.380 align:middle line:84%
of bonding deeply with
other men is actually

00:07:20.380 --> 00:07:21.900 align:middle line:90%
a need that men have.

00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:23.510 align:middle line:84%
And if they fulfill
that need, they

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:27.210 align:middle line:84%
become deeper, more
accountable, happier men.

00:07:27.210 --> 00:07:29.304 align:middle line:84%
Now, the little
illustration we give

00:07:29.304 --> 00:07:31.470 align:middle line:84%
in the book about this,
which I think really kind of

00:07:31.470 --> 00:07:35.120 align:middle line:84%
shines a light on
it, most men, if they

00:07:35.120 --> 00:07:38.210 align:middle line:84%
were having a conflict or
difficulty in marriage,

00:07:38.210 --> 00:07:40.900 align:middle line:84%
would not hesitate to go
for counseling, right?

00:07:40.900 --> 00:07:44.330 align:middle line:84%
Most men, if they had a
challenge with a teenage child,

00:07:44.330 --> 00:07:46.510 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't hesitate to
go for counseling.

00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:48.440 align:middle line:84%
If you had a challenge
with a coworker,

00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:50.540 align:middle line:84%
you would see mediation
as appropriate.

00:07:50.540 --> 00:07:54.290 align:middle line:84%
But it's very rare for a man to
have conflict with another man

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:56.979 align:middle line:84%
and to be willing to get help to
resolve it or to go to therapy

00:07:56.979 --> 00:07:59.020 align:middle line:84%
because you're having a
problem your best friend.

00:07:59.020 --> 00:07:59.650 align:middle line:90%
You wouldn't do that.

00:07:59.650 --> 00:08:00.670 align:middle line:90%
It would be weird.

00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:03.365 align:middle line:84%
A woman, on the other hand,
might be willing to do that.

00:08:03.365 --> 00:08:04.740 align:middle line:84%
But you see, that's
because we're

00:08:04.740 --> 00:08:07.210 align:middle line:84%
so deeply conditioned
to not value

00:08:07.210 --> 00:08:08.760 align:middle line:90%
our friendships with other men.

00:08:08.760 --> 00:08:12.300 align:middle line:84%
And actually, that's a
really pivotal, pivotal thing

00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:13.880 align:middle line:84%
in being able to
grow, because a man

00:08:13.880 --> 00:08:16.970 align:middle line:84%
needs the challenge and
the support of other men

00:08:16.970 --> 00:08:18.240 align:middle line:90%
to be able to fully blossom.

00:08:18.240 --> 00:08:20.980 align:middle line:84%
He's not going to be able
to get that from his wife

00:08:20.980 --> 00:08:21.840 align:middle line:90%
or from a woman.

00:08:21.840 --> 00:08:22.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:26.290 align:middle line:84%
And you bring up in the
book that in the past,

00:08:26.290 --> 00:08:31.090 align:middle line:84%
men's status in society,
their heroism, so to speak,

00:08:31.090 --> 00:08:36.380 align:middle line:84%
came from unconscious patterns,
where you were inducted

00:08:36.380 --> 00:08:38.820 align:middle line:84%
into the military,
for example, you

00:08:38.820 --> 00:08:41.500 align:middle line:84%
were following in your
father's footsteps

00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.330 align:middle line:90%
as a blacksmith in your work.

00:08:43.330 --> 00:08:45.560 align:middle line:84%
And your life was
defined for you,

00:08:45.560 --> 00:08:48.200 align:middle line:84%
but it was never a
conscious choice.

00:08:48.200 --> 00:08:50.110 align:middle line:84%
And this was a
really good point.

00:08:50.110 --> 00:08:53.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it struck
me that now that we

00:08:53.140 --> 00:08:55.930 align:middle line:84%
have the possibility
of conscious choice,

00:08:55.930 --> 00:08:59.250 align:middle line:84%
it requires men to become
completely conscious

00:08:59.250 --> 00:09:00.200 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:09:00.200 --> 00:09:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Right.

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:03.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm just having a little
bit of a shock here

00:09:03.660 --> 00:09:05.740 align:middle line:84%
because it's unusual for
me to do an interview

00:09:05.740 --> 00:09:07.656 align:middle line:84%
where someone's read the
book this thoroughly.

00:09:07.656 --> 00:09:09.370 align:middle line:84%
It's like, wow,
you've read the book.

00:09:09.370 --> 00:09:09.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yes.

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:10.750 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So many interviewers,
they've skimmed it.

00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:11.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I always do.

00:09:11.750 --> 00:09:12.830 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: But you've
really gone through deeply.

00:09:12.830 --> 00:09:13.450 align:middle line:90%
That's very nice.

00:09:13.450 --> 00:09:14.370 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:09:14.370 --> 00:09:16.340 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you're making
a good point.

